Excessive requirements for public procurement applications will be excluded by law
The legislation may lay down exhaustive requirements for requests to participate in procurement.
In the autumn session at the plenary session, the State Duma plans to consider in the second reading a bill establishing the requirements for the content and composition of the application for participation in the procurement, the participants of which can be only small and medium-sized businesses.
Amendments are made by the government to the law "On the purchase of goods, works, services by certain types of legal entities".
The bill was developed in compliance with the road map for the implementation of the Strategy for the Development of Small and Medium Enterprises in the Russian Federation until 2030, approved by the government.
It provides for the preparation of a draft law on the exhaustive list of documents that customers are entitled to request in the form of an application from participants in the procurement - entities of small and medium-sized enterprises.
And also on the list of requirements for these documents.
To date, the law "On the purchase of goods, works, services by certain types of legal entities" regulates the purchasing activities of certain types of legal entities.
Requirements for the content, form, design and composition of the application for participation in the purchase are established by the customers themselves in the procurement documentation.
"As a result, customers establish excessive requirements for the content, registration of the application, mandatory availability in its composition of references, certificates, extracts, the period of receipt of which in the authorized bodies will be compared to the period of submission of applications, which leads to the impossibility of participation in such purchases.
The new bill provides for the establishment of an exhaustive list of documents that customers are entitled to request in the form of an application from participants in the procurement, who are subjects of small and medium-sized enterprises.
"The adoption of the document will eliminate the arbitrary establishment by customers of requirements for the composition and content of applications of participants who are subjects of small and medium-sized enterprises," - said in the explanatory note.
