Woman dumped her husband's body in a pit and poured concrete under Belgorod
In the Belgorod region, the woman confessed to the murder of her husband, who she dumped in a pit with waste and poured concrete, according to the website of the regional administration of the SC of the Russian Federation.
It is noted that the suspect has been married to the murderer since 1999.
In recent years, the husband began to abuse alcohol and after another quarrel, the woman decided to kill.
"When the husband fell asleep, the suspect tied his hands and feet, put a plastic bag on his head and pressed a pillow.
When the husband stopped giving signs of life, she wrapped the body in a carpet, carried it out into the yard and hid it in a burrow.
The next day, she called a concrete mixer and poured concrete into the pit," the management said.
The woman later said her husband was missing.
Relatives of the deceased turned to the police, who opened the pit and removed the body.
The investigation is intended to request the court to arrest the suspect.
The criminal investigation is currently underway.
